    <h3>Community Information</h3>
    <p>Considered part of the Southern region of the United States, King William, Virginia is located just 31 miles from Richmond, the state capital.  There is much to do locally, and also in the nearby big city of Richmond.  Known for its large retail selection, rich culture, fine dining and historic sites, Richmond is the perfect place to discover.  With a number of museums, galleries, theaters and sport stadiums, there is something for everyone to enjoy.  Back at King William, the beautiful landscape includes rivers, farmlands and timber ands in a friendly environment.  With low crime rates, a relaxed pace of life and a sense of hometown friendliness, King William offers the best of small town fun with a big city feel!
</p>
